  "local_port": 34508,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do bottle caps work in Pokemon Sun / Moon?",
  "response": "In *Pok\u00e9mon Sun* and *Pok\u00e9mon Moon*, bottle caps are special items used to improve a Pok\u00e9mon's **Individual Values (IVs)**. IVs are hidden stats that determine a Pok\u00e9mon's potential in each stat (HP, Attack, Defense, Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed). Bottle caps allow you to maximize these IVs without needing to breed or catch a new Pok\u00e9mon.\n\nHere\u2019s how bottle caps work in the games:\n\n---\n\n### **Types of Bottle Caps**\n1. **Regular Bottle Cap**:\n   - Increases one selected IV of a Pok\u00e9mon to its maximum value (31).\n   - You can choose which stat to maximize.\n\n2. **Gold Bottle Cap**:\n   - Increases **all** IVs of a Pok\u00e9mon to their maximum values (31).\n   - This is more efficient but also rarer.\n\n---\n\n### **Using Bottle Caps**\nTo use bottle caps, you need to visit the **Hyper Training** feature, which is unlocked after defeating the Elite Four and becoming the Champion. Hyper Training is conducted by an NPC named **Mr. Hyper** who can be found at the **Harbor Freight (Pok\u00e9mon Center)** in **Mount Lanakila**.\n\n### **Requirements for Hyper Training**:\n- The Pok\u00e9mon must be **level 100**.\n- You must have a bottle cap (regular or gold) to use.\n\n### **Steps to Hyper Train**:\n1. Bring your level 100 Pok\u00e9mon to Mr. Hyper.\n2. Choose the stat(s) you want to maximize using a regular bottle cap or use a gold bottle cap to max all stats.\n3. Confirm the process, and the Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s IVs will be boosted to their maximum.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**\n- Bottle caps do not permanently change the Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s IVs. Instead, they simulate having perfect IVs for the purposes of battles and stat calculations. The original IVs remain unchanged for breeding purposes.\n- Bottle caps are finite resources, but you can obtain them in various ways:\n  - **Battle Tree** (purchased with Battle Points).\n  - **Island Scan** (chance to find them).\n  - **Festival Plaza** (from certain shops or missions).\n  - **Pok\u00e9 Pelago** (rarely found in the Isle Aphun).\n\n---\n\nBy using bottle caps, you can optimize your Pok\u00e9mon for competitive battles without needing to spend time breeding for perfect IVs.",
